<plot>The booming garment industry in Cambodia made Chea Vichea, the president of the main worker's union, one of the country's most popular leaders. This film, shot as events unfolded over four years, explores the possible motives for his assassination and unravels the police plot that framed two men, now serving 20 years for a crime committed by others. In the course of this investigation, we begin to see the relationship between globalization, corruption and repression in developing countries.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?655098</url></doc>
